スイスの女性は堕胎を自由に 中文 (zh) 瑞士女性对堕胎的看法

The survey, carried out by the gfs.bern research institute, found that 60% of women in Switzerland believe that abortion should be legal in all cases, while 30% believe it should be legal in some cases.

The survey also found that 70% of women believe that abortion should be a private matter, while 20% believe it should be a public matter.

The survey was carried out in March and April 2019 among 1,000 women aged 18 and over.

The results come as the Swiss parliament is debating a bill that would allow women to have an abortion up to 12 weeks into a pregnancy. The bill is expected to be voted on in the autumn.
